I begin reading the instructions in Edureka's Github tutorial.
The page looks cluttered.
Github looks cluttered.
The interfaces of these two websites stirs up some anxiety within me, but I attempt to overlook it and push forward.
...
The tutorial is now explaining branches.
This doesn't seem complicated to me, but something about the lack of visual representation within Github feels uncomfortable.
I want to be able to tell, at a glance, that I'm not working in the main branch.
It doesn't seem like that's quite what the UI designers had in mind.
This oversight on their part has yet to do me in, so I will press on.
...
